\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{Res}\Bigl(f, i\sqrt{3-2\sqrt{2}}\Bigr)
&=\frac{4\,i\sqrt{3-2\sqrt{2}}}{\,i\Bigl(4\bigl(i\sqrt{3-2\sqrt{2}}\bigr)^3+12\bigl(i\sqrt{3-2\sqrt{2}}\bigr)\Bigr)}
=\frac{4\,i\sqrt{3-2\sqrt{2}}}{\,i\Bigl(4i^3(3-2\sqrt{2})^{3/2}+12\,i\sqrt{3-2\sqrt{2}}\Bigr)}\\[1mm]
&=\frac{4\,i\sqrt{3-2\sqrt{2}}}{-4i^2(3-2\sqrt{2})^{3/2}+12i^2\sqrt{3-2\sqrt{2}}}
=\frac{4\,i\sqrt{3-2\sqrt{2}}}{4(3-2\sqrt{2})^{3/2}-12\sqrt{3-2\sqrt{2}}}\\[1mm]
&=\frac{4\,i\sqrt{3-2\sqrt{2}}}{4\sqrt{3-2\sqrt{2}}\Bigl[(3-2\sqrt{2})-3\Bigr]}
=\frac{4\,i}{4\Bigl[-2\sqrt{2}\Bigr]}
=-\frac{i}{2\sqrt{2}}.
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{Note that for } f(z)=\frac{4z}{i(z^4+6z^2+1)},\text{ the residue at a simple pole } z_0 \text{ is } \text{Res}(f,z_0)=\frac{4z_0}{i\,(4z_0^3+12z_0)}
=\frac{1}{i\,(z_0^2+3)}.\\[1mm]
\text{For } z_0^2=-\left(3-2\sqrt{2}\right),\text{ we have } z_0^2+3=3-\left(3-2\sqrt{2}\right)=2\sqrt{2}.\\[1mm]
\text{Thus, both residues at } z=\pm i\sqrt{3-2\sqrt{2}} \text{ equal } \frac{1}{i\,(2\sqrt{2})}=-\frac{i}{2\sqrt{2}},\\[1mm]
\text{so their sum is } -\frac{i}{2\sqrt{2}}-\frac{i}{2\sqrt{2}}=-\frac{i}{\sqrt{2}},\\[1mm]
\text{and by the residue theorem, the integral equals } 2\pi i\left(-\frac{i}{\sqrt{2}}\right)=\frac{2\pi}{\sqrt{2}}=\pi\sqrt{2}.
\end{aligned}
\]

Step 2: Consider the prime factorization of \(i\). If \(i = p_1^{e_1} p_2^{e_2} \cdots p_k^{e_k}\), then \(2i = 2^1 p_1^{e_1} p_2^{e_2} \cdots p_k^{e_k}\). The number of divisors of \(2i\) is \((1+1)(e_1+1)(e_2+1)\cdots(e_k+1)\). Similarly, if \(a_i = q_1^{f_1} q_2^{f_2} \cdots q_m^{f_m}\), then \(2a_i = 2^1 q_1^{f_1} q_2^{f_2} \cdots q_m^{f_m}\), and the number of divisors of \(2a_i\) is \((1+1)(f_1+1)(f_2+1)\cdots(f_m+1)\). Since \(2i\) and \(2a_i\) have the same number of divisors, we must have \((1+1)(e_1+1)(e_2+1)\cdots(e_k+1) = (1+1)(f_1+1)(f_2+1)\cdots(f_m+1)\), which simplifies to \((e_1+1)(e_2+1)\cdots(e_k+1) = (f_1+1)(f_2+1)\cdots(f_m+1)\).

Given this, the simplest solution is \(a_i = i\), as it preserves the number of divisors. Therefore, the sequence \(a_i = i\) satisfies the condition.

